      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Tuesday: 5 to 15 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, has fallen above approximately 2000 m. The new snow and wind slabs are lying on soft layers in particular on wind-protected shady slopes. <br/> Faceted weak layers exist in the old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes. <br/> Several medium-sized slab avalanches have been released in the last few days. On Friday on steep slopes small and medium-sized avalanches occurred naturally."
      },
